      • parseTCP

        public java.lang.String parseTCP(java.lang.String message)
        Interfaced method to parse TCP message socket callback is triggered by incoming message. Used for messages about cost and timing requests, initial startup connection, the startpoint and current map settings, new job request information (next waypoint) or an mandatory update on the current position.
        Specified by:
        parseTCP in interface TCPListener
        Parameters:
        message - Received TCP socket message string
        Returns:
        A return answer to be send back over the socket to the Core.

      • jobRequest

        private void jobRequest(WayPoint nextPoint)
        Method called for when a job request is received from the core. It contains the next waypoint to drive to. Given we are dealing with a simulated vehicle a request will be made to the RosServer to calculate how long the actual driving would take to the next waypoint. Then it will use this estimated time to simulate the driving.
        Parameters:
        nextPoint - Coordinates of the next waypoint to drive to. *

      • calculateCost

        private void calculateCost(java.util.ArrayList<Point> points)
        Method called for when a cost calculation request is received from the core. It contains a list of waypoints(2) to calculate the cost between. This is as simulated vehicle so it can't calculate this cost itself. It will do a REST request to the RosServer to calculate the estimated times between the current position and the starting location of the route, and between that starting location and the end location of the route.
        Parameters:
        points - List of the Point object class containing the 2 points to calculate the weights. (starting and end)

      • calculateTiming

        private void calculateTiming(java.util.ArrayList<Point> points)
        Method called for when a timing calculation request is received from the core. It contains a list of waypoints(2) to calculate the cost between. This is as simulated vehicle so it can't calculate these timings itself. It will do a REST request to the RosServer to calculate the estimated times between the current position and the starting location of the route, and between that starting location and the end location of the route.
        Parameters:
        points - List of the Point object class containing the 2 points to calculate the timings. (starting and end)

      • calcWeightROS

        private Cost calcWeightROS(java.util.ArrayList<Point> points)
        This method is used by calculateCost en calculateTiming to request the weight between waypoints from a Ros server. If the same request was made previously, the cost will be returned from a local list.
        Parameters:
        points - List of the Point object class containing the 2 points to calculate the timings. (starting and end)
        Returns:
        object of the Cost class which contains the calculated costs
